<div1 type="letter">

<pb facs="nei.j4a.35.1.001" />
<fw type="curatorial">1</fw>
<note type="curatorial"></note>

<fw type="letterhead">THE STATE OF COLORADO
POET LAUREATE
MILFORD E. SHIELDS
P.O. BOX 1217
DURANBO, COLORADO, U.S.A.
81301</fw>
<opener>
<dateline>January 2, 1972
</dateline>
<address>
<addrLine>Dr. John G. Neihardt, Poet Laureate</addrLine>
<addrLine>State of Nebraska </addrLine>
<addrLine>5835 Vine Street</addrLine>
<addrLine>Lincoln, Nebraska 68505</addrLine> 
</address>
<salute>Dear Dr. Neihardt:</salute>
</opener>

<p>Your Christmas greeting was indeed a very rare inspiration. The explanation of your Indian name raised me to the height of the Rainbow.</p>
<p>Here is my salutation to you:

<lg><l>Your poetry God's witness is,</l>
<l>Your lines are living words of His,</l>
<l>Your spirit of the cosmic flame</l>
<l>That He sealed with the "Naihardt Name."</l></lg></p>
<p>May I wish to you and yours a most happy and prosperous New Year.</p>

<closer>
<salute>Very sincerely yours,</salute>
<signed>Milford E. Shields</signed>
<note type="authorial">Milford E. Shields</note>
</closer>

</div1>
</body>

